    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-07-01T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-07-01T02:00:00-05:00" n="196"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">794A.00/7–150: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">All Diplomatic and Certain Consular Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d196fn1">In addition to all American diplomatic missions,
                        this telegram was sent to the Consulates General in Hong Kong and
                        Singapore.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-07-01T03:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 1, 1950—3 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In event you queried by Govt to which you accredited or by ur dipl colleagues re
                    significance that part Pres’s Jun 27 statement which deals with Formosa, fol gen
                    views Dept may be helpful:</p>
                <p>Action to prevent attack on Formosa and to prevent Natl Govt air and sea
                    operations against mainland taken as immediate security measure to preserve
                    peace in Pacific and without prejudice to pol questions <pb facs="0382" n="368"
                        xml:id="pg_368"/> affecting Chi Govt. No change anticipated in relations
                    between US Govt and Chi Govt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
